cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with human pose tracking in video frames. The use of machine learning techniques for learning spatiotemporal relationships among joints also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of attention mechanisms to attend only to relevant areas in the video frames suggests that it could belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of relational cues in the spatial and temporal domains also suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of 3D body pose tracking, 3D hand pose tracking, and 3D hand gesture tracking suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
